WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.133
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.133 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:11.500
♪ WANDERING DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:11.500 --> 00:12.700
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.700 --> 00:14.867
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.867 --> 00:18.834
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS
STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.834 --> 00:22.000
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:26.000 --> 00:27.934
YOU KNOW, I JUST WANT
TO THANK YOU BOTH

00:27.934 --> 00:30.500
FOR CONVINCING ERIC
TO MOVE BACK IN WITH US.

00:36.200 --> 00:38.500
YOU KNOW,
IT'S REALLY GREAT TO
HAVE YOU BACK, BUDDY.

00:38.500 --> 00:39.734
WELL, YOU
KNOW SOMETHING?

00:39.734 --> 00:40.734
I'M HAPPY
TO BE BACK.

00:48.033 --> 00:49.934
NICE KISS.

00:49.934 --> 00:51.600
THANK YOU, JACK.

00:55.500 --> 00:57.033
YOU SEE, SHAWN...

00:57.033 --> 00:58.500
ALL IT TOOK
WAS YOU AND ME

00:58.500 --> 00:59.667
TO GET THEM TO
SETTLE THEIR DIFFERENCES.

00:59.667 --> 01:01.767
CORY AND SHAWN
FOREVER.

01:01.767 --> 01:02.834
BEST FRIENDS.

01:02.834 --> 01:05.100
BEST FRIENDS FOREVER.

01:08.600 --> 01:11.300
CORY, WHY ARE YOU
LOOKING AT ME LIKE THAT?

01:11.300 --> 01:12.467
CORY, WHAT--

01:14.400 --> 01:15.800
CORY.

01:21.033 --> 01:22.600
AAAHHH!

01:24.300 --> 01:25.300
CORY.

01:25.300 --> 01:26.567
SHAWN.

01:26.567 --> 01:30.000
DON'T TELL ME.
IS IT THE PUPPET
NIGHTMARE AGAIN?

01:30.000 --> 01:32.800
YEAH, IT WAS
THE PUPPET NIGHTMARE.

01:32.800 --> 01:35.367
HE WAS CHASING ME
ON FOOT.

01:35.367 --> 01:37.200
HE HAD A GUN.

01:37.200 --> 01:40.500
WOW. YOU OK?

01:40.500 --> 01:43.567
YEAH, I'M OK.

01:43.567 --> 01:46.200
WELL, GOOD.
LET'S GET SOME SLEEP.

01:46.200 --> 01:47.700
I GOT THAT SPEECH
FOR FEENY TOMORROW.

01:47.700 --> 01:49.834
I'VE GOT TO BE FRESH
IF I'M GONNA FAKE IT.

01:49.834 --> 01:50.934
OK.

01:52.300 --> 01:54.367
GOOD NIGHT, COR.

01:54.367 --> 01:56.200
NIGHTY NIGHT, SHAWN.

01:58.133 --> 01:59.133
SHAWN?

01:59.133 --> 02:00.400
YEAH, COR?

02:00.400 --> 02:02.400
YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND.

02:03.967 --> 02:05.600
THANKS, COR.

02:11.734 --> 02:13.367
NOW WATCH CLOSELY

02:13.367 --> 02:16.400
AS I SLOWLY POUR
THE MILK INTO THE HAT.

02:16.400 --> 02:20.567
MR. HUNTER, YOUR SPEECH
IS ON LOUIS PASTEUR.

02:20.567 --> 02:23.700
I DON'T SEE WHAT
THAT HAS TO DO WITH
MAKING MILK DISAPPEAR.

02:23.700 --> 02:26.100
THIS HAS EVERYTHING
TO DO WITH LOU.
TRUST ME.

02:26.100 --> 02:28.133
NOW DOES ANYONE
IN THE AUDIENCE

02:28.133 --> 02:30.000
HAPPEN TO HAVE
A PIECE OF
MAGIC ROPE?

02:34.200 --> 02:36.867
LOOK AT THAT.
MR. MATTHEWS...

02:36.867 --> 02:38.567
WHY DON'T YOU
COME DOWN HERE.

02:38.567 --> 02:40.834
I HATE TEACHING.

02:40.834 --> 02:43.200
MAY I PLEASE HAVE
THAT MAGIC ROPE?

02:43.200 --> 02:44.500
YES, YOU MAY.

02:44.500 --> 02:45.867
NOW,
WHAT A LOT OF PEOPLE
DON'T KNOW ABOUT LOU--

02:53.100 --> 02:55.367
AAAAHHH! AAAAHHH!

02:59.367 --> 03:01.400
THAT LITTLE CURLY-HEADED
BOYFRIEND OF YOURS

03:01.400 --> 03:02.967
IS DRIVING ME INSANE.

03:02.967 --> 03:05.133
IS HE STILL
HAVING NIGHTMARES?

03:05.133 --> 03:06.934
NO, NO, NO.
NOT ANYMORE.

03:06.934 --> 03:09.200
HE HASN'T SLEPT
IN 3 DAYS.

03:09.200 --> 03:10.667
I TURN OFF THE LIGHTS...

03:10.667 --> 03:13.467
AND I HEAR HIM MOVING AROUND
IN THE DARK LIKE A RAT.

03:13.467 --> 03:16.233
I WAKE UP THE NEXT MORNING,
THE CLOSETS ARE REORGANIZED,

03:16.233 --> 03:19.934
MY SHORTS ARE IRONED,
AND MY HAIR'S BEEN MOUSSED.

03:19.934 --> 03:21.667
OH, MY
POOR CORY.

03:21.667 --> 03:23.033
HOT COFFEE
COMING THROUGH.

03:23.033 --> 03:24.567
HEY, THANKS, COR.

03:24.567 --> 03:26.500
THESE ARE MINE.
GET YOUR OWN.

03:26.500 --> 03:29.867
CORY, DRINKING COFFEE
TO AVOID YOUR NIGHTMARES
IS NOT THE SOLUTION.

03:29.867 --> 03:31.700
WHO SAID I WAS
HAVING NIGHTMARES?

03:31.700 --> 03:33.934
I DID, YOU LOONY!

03:33.934 --> 03:35.667
WHY WOULD YOU SAY
I WAS HAVING NIGHT--

03:36.834 --> 03:40.934
OH, I'M NOT MAD
AT YOU. NOT YOU.

03:40.934 --> 03:42.500
NOT SHAWNY SHAWN.

03:42.500 --> 03:45.567
HEY, HOW'S THE MOUSSE
HOLDING UP, HUH?

03:45.567 --> 03:48.033
IT LOOKS GOOD,
YES IT DOES.

03:49.767 --> 03:50.834
ERIC...

03:50.834 --> 03:53.600
MMM, XENA,
MY WARRIOR PRINCESS.

03:53.600 --> 03:55.033
ERIC!

03:55.033 --> 03:58.800
AWW, YOU'RE NOT
MY WARRIOR PRINCESS,
YOU'RE MY MOMMY.

03:58.800 --> 04:00.767
HONEY, YOU SLEEPING
ON THE COUCH

04:00.767 --> 04:02.233
IS JUST NOT
WORKING OUT.

04:02.233 --> 04:03.500
AND WHOSE FAULT IS THAT?

04:03.500 --> 04:07.834
TURNING MY ROOM INTO
A NURSERY FOR HIM.

04:07.834 --> 04:09.500
YOU KNOW SOMETHING,
MORGAN, YOU'VE
GOT A BIG ROOM.

04:09.500 --> 04:10.500
WOULDN'T IT
BE FUN IF--

04:10.500 --> 04:11.900
NO.
BUT, BUT...

04:11.900 --> 04:12.967
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT--

04:12.967 --> 04:14.500
NO.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.100
HEY, CORY, CORY,
CORY, WAIT.

04:16.100 --> 04:18.300
YOU KNOW, WE'VE GOT
AN HOUR BEFORE CLASS.

04:18.300 --> 04:19.767
WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE A NAP?

04:19.767 --> 04:21.667
I DON'T NEED
A NAP, I NEED
TO PAINT A HOUSE.

04:21.667 --> 04:24.000
I'LL RACE YOU
TO THE DOOR.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.033
I WIN, I WIN.

04:28.500 --> 04:29.400
ERIC?

04:31.000 --> 04:32.467
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

04:32.467 --> 04:35.867
I'VE DECIDED TO LIVE
WITH YOU GUYS.

04:35.867 --> 04:37.200
YOU KNOW,
I JUST THINK IT'D BE
SO GREAT, YOU KNOW,

04:37.200 --> 04:39.934
TO HAVE THIS
GREAT BROTHER
AND BROTHER'S FRIEND

04:39.934 --> 04:42.000
AND I THINK
THE 3 OF US TOGETHER,

04:42.000 --> 04:43.200
WE REALLY WOULD BE...

04:54.567 --> 04:55.667
HELLO, ROOMIE!

04:55.667 --> 04:56.667
AAAAH!

04:56.667 --> 04:57.700
ROOMIE?

04:58.900 --> 05:01.300
OH, JACK, LOOK.
IT'S A HOMELESS MAN.

05:01.300 --> 05:02.900
OH, HOW SAD.

05:02.900 --> 05:04.400
YEAH, THE POOR GUY.

05:06.667 --> 05:08.300
ERIC.

05:08.300 --> 05:09.300
MORNING.

05:09.300 --> 05:10.834
ERIC, GET UP RIGHT NOW.

05:10.834 --> 05:13.200
YOU ARE COMING
BACK HOME WITH US.
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.500
NO, I DON'T
WANT YOUR PITY.

05:15.500 --> 05:18.233
OH, COME ON, MAN.
YOU CAN HAVE
YOUR OLD ROOM BACK.

05:18.233 --> 05:19.767
YOU HAVEN'T
RENTED IT OUT YET?

05:19.767 --> 05:20.800
NO.

05:20.800 --> 05:22.000
REALLY?

05:22.000 --> 05:23.867
NO. WE'VE BEEN HOPING
YOU'D COME BACK HOME.

05:23.867 --> 05:24.934
RIGHT, HON?

05:24.934 --> 05:27.033
A--AH. HON?

05:27.033 --> 05:29.700
HON? IS THAT WHAT
I'M GONNA BE HEARING
24 HOURS A WEEK, HUH?

05:29.700 --> 05:31.867
OH, COME ON, ERIC.

05:31.867 --> 05:34.233
OH, I GET IT.
I'M ERIC,
BUT YOU'RE HON.

05:35.567 --> 05:37.000
LOOKING FOR A ROOMMATE!

05:37.000 --> 05:37.934
ERIC, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

05:37.934 --> 05:38.900
WHAT AM I DOING?
I'M BEING A MAN.

05:38.900 --> 05:40.500
I AM STANDING ON
MY OWN 2 FEET.

05:40.500 --> 05:42.400
I'M GONNA HOLD ON
TO A LITTLE BIT
OF MY DIGNITY.

05:42.400 --> 05:47.000
PLEASE! SOMEONE
TAKE PITY UPON
MY WRETCHED SOUL!

05:48.667 --> 05:49.967
I'M LOOKING
FOR A ROOMMATE.

05:49.967 --> 05:51.567
HEY, I WAS LOOKING FIRST.

05:51.567 --> 05:53.100
NO, I MEAN,
I HAVE AN APARTMENT.

05:53.100 --> 05:54.467
I'M LOOKING FOR
SOMEONE TO SHARE IT.

05:54.467 --> 05:55.867
OH, HEY, GOOD LUCK
TO YOU, THEN.

05:55.867 --> 05:57.767
LOOKING FOR A ROOMMATE!

06:00.600 --> 06:02.200
ALL RIGHT, NOW, LET'S
CONTINUE OUR DISCUSSION

06:02.200 --> 06:05.033
OF WILLIAM SHAKESPEARE'S
<i>HAMLET. </i>

06:05.033 --> 06:06.033
MR. MATTHEWS!

06:06.033 --> 06:08.100
MR. MATTHEWS.

06:08.100 --> 06:10.033
MR. MATTHEWS,
I WOULD APPRECIATE IT

06:10.033 --> 06:12.900
IF YOU WOULD
STAY CONSCIOUS
DURING MY CLASS.

06:12.900 --> 06:14.300
I'M CONSCIOUS.

06:14.300 --> 06:15.500
WONDERFUL.

06:15.500 --> 06:18.300
NOW WHERE WERE WE?

06:18.300 --> 06:19.934
AH, YES.

06:19.934 --> 06:23.600
"TO SLEEP,
PERCHANCE TO DREAM.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.667
"AY, THERE'S THE RUB.

06:25.667 --> 06:27.000
FOR IN THAT SLEEP
OF DEATH..."

06:27.000 --> 06:28.300
[WHISPERING]
Shawn.

06:28.300 --> 06:30.667
SHAWN, YOU CAN'T
LET ME GO TO SLEEP.

06:30.667 --> 06:31.700
SHAWN?

06:33.367 --> 06:34.567
GREAT.

06:34.567 --> 06:36.100
[BELL RINGS]

06:38.467 --> 06:44.467
THAT'S RIGHT.
SCURRY OFF TO YOUR
MUNDANE LITTLE LIVES.

06:44.467 --> 06:46.467
MR. MATTHEWS...

06:48.667 --> 06:51.600
YOU ARE ACTING VERY ODD.

06:51.600 --> 06:54.400
I'VE BEEN HAVING
DREAMS, MR. FEENY...

06:54.400 --> 06:59.100
DREAMS ABOUT
KILLING SOMEONE
VERY CLOSE TO ME.

06:59.100 --> 07:00.400
MR. HUNTER.

07:00.400 --> 07:04.000
YES, YES!
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

07:04.000 --> 07:05.467
YOU ARE BRILLIANT.

07:05.467 --> 07:06.500
IT'S BEEN KILLING ME,

07:06.500 --> 07:07.934
I HAVEN'T BEEN
ABLE TO SLEEP.

07:07.934 --> 07:09.667
THERE'S NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT, CORY.

07:09.667 --> 07:12.867
KILLING YOUR BEST
FRIEND IS A COMMON
THEME IN DREAMS.

07:12.867 --> 07:14.233
IT'S PERFECTLY NORMAL.

07:14.233 --> 07:16.133
WELL, HOW NORMAL?

07:16.133 --> 07:17.767
BECAUSE, YOU SEE,
I HAVE THIS ONE DREAM

07:17.767 --> 07:19.000
WHERE I PUSH SHAWN--

07:19.000 --> 07:22.133
DOWN AN EMPTY
ELEVATOR SHAFT.

07:22.133 --> 07:23.600
YES!

07:23.600 --> 07:27.000
THE ELEVATOR SHAFT
REPRESENTS
THE UPS AND DOWNS

07:27.000 --> 07:29.500
OF YOUR FRIENDSHIP
WITH MR. HUNTER.

07:29.500 --> 07:32.033
UPS AND DOWNS.
THAT'S INTERESTING.

07:32.033 --> 07:34.133
YOU SEE, MR. HUNTER,
IN HIS SEARCH

07:34.133 --> 07:38.834
FOR PEACE AND HARMONY
IN HIS LIFE,
CAUSES YOU PAIN.

07:38.834 --> 07:39.934
HOW?

07:39.934 --> 07:40.967
BY PUTTING

07:40.967 --> 07:42.500
AN INCREDIBLE AMOUNT
OF PRESSURE ON YOU

07:42.500 --> 07:44.200
TO HELP HIM
IN HIS SEARCH.

07:45.300 --> 07:47.967
ANNOYING, ISN'T IT?

07:47.967 --> 07:50.100
SO HOW DO I STOP
THESE DREAMS?

07:50.100 --> 07:51.200
YOU FORGIVE HIM.

07:51.200 --> 07:53.767
FORGIVENESS, OF COURSE.

07:53.767 --> 07:57.000
HE HURT YOU, AND NOW
YOU'RE HURTING HIM BACK.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.600
FORGIVE AND
THE DREAMS WILL STOP.

08:00.600 --> 08:02.900
OK. THANK YOU,
MR. FEENY.

08:02.900 --> 08:04.867
ANYTIME, MR. MATTHEWS,
ANYTIME.

08:09.133 --> 08:10.400
WELL, WHAT'S THAT?

08:10.400 --> 08:12.233
HEY, YOU KNOW HOW
I DIDN'T GET YOU

08:12.233 --> 08:13.767
A BIRTHDAY PRESENT
LAST YEAR?

08:13.767 --> 08:16.100
WELL, HERE YOU GO.

08:16.100 --> 08:19.133
SHAWN, I HAVE TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

08:19.133 --> 08:21.000
TELL ME AFTER YOU
OPEN THE PRESENT.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.300
WELL, OK.

08:23.400 --> 08:29.900
WOW. MY OWN PERSONALIZED
BASEBALL BAT.

08:29.900 --> 08:31.467
TOO COOL.

08:32.700 --> 08:34.600
[BASEBALL
ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING]

08:40.700 --> 08:42.700
DIE, SHAWN, DIE!

09:00.066 --> 09:01.567
YOU HAVE TO
LET ME EXPLAIN.

09:01.567 --> 09:02.800
EXPLAIN WHAT?

09:02.800 --> 09:05.000
MY BEST FRIEND SCREAMS
HE WANTS TO KILL ME

09:05.000 --> 09:06.100
IN FRONT OF
THE WHOLE CLASS?

09:06.100 --> 09:07.100
WHAT'S TO EXPLAIN?

09:07.100 --> 09:09.100
WELL, I LIED ABOUT
THE PUPPET DREAM.

09:09.100 --> 09:10.734
NO KIDDING.

09:10.734 --> 09:12.767
THESE ARE NOT
GOOD DREAMS
I'M HAVING, SHAWN.

09:12.767 --> 09:14.233
I KILL YOU IN
EVERY ONE OF THEM.

09:14.233 --> 09:15.367
I KILL YOU GOOD.

09:15.367 --> 09:16.567
LIKE HOW?

09:16.567 --> 09:18.867
WELL, I FED YOU
THUMBTACK SOUP.

09:18.867 --> 09:21.033
I POURED HOT LAVA
DOWN YOUR PANTS.

09:21.033 --> 09:23.500
I PULLED YOUR
HEART OUT WITH
SALAD TONGS.

09:23.500 --> 09:25.400
I SET FIRE
TO YOUR TIE.

09:25.400 --> 09:27.900
I SHREDDED YOU OVER PASTA
WITH A CHEESE GRATER.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.600
I DRESSED YOU UP
LIKE A ROOSTER

09:29.600 --> 09:31.734
AND ENTERED YOU
IN A COCKFIGHT.

09:31.734 --> 09:33.100
HMMM. HOW'D I DO?

09:33.100 --> 09:34.400
WELL, YOU WON, HA HA...

09:34.400 --> 09:37.200
BUT THE CROWD CRIED FIX
AND IT GOT UGLY.

09:37.200 --> 09:39.400
I'M SORRY, SHAWN.

09:39.400 --> 09:42.967
THEY'RE DREAMS.
GET SOME SLEEP.

09:42.967 --> 09:46.133
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I THINK THERE
MAY BE A SOLUTION.

09:46.133 --> 09:47.934
IN MY LAST DREAM,
FEENY WAS THERE.

09:47.934 --> 09:49.734
HE TOLD ME
ALL I HAD TO DO
TO STOP THESE DREAMS

09:49.734 --> 09:51.000
WAS TO FORGIVE YOU.

09:51.000 --> 09:53.400
FORGIVE ME FOR WHAT?

09:53.400 --> 09:55.300
WELL, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S IMPORTANT.

09:55.300 --> 09:58.300
WHAT'S IMPORTANT
IS I FORGIVE YOU,
SHAWN, OK?

09:58.300 --> 10:03.667
YOU'RE FORGIVEN,
100% FORGIVEN,
FORGIVEN, FORGIVEN.

10:03.667 --> 10:06.800
AND NOW I'M ALL BETTER.

10:06.800 --> 10:08.200
SO YOU'RE GOING
TO SLEEP TONIGHT?

10:08.200 --> 10:09.767
OH YEAH.
THANKS TO MR. FEENY,

10:09.767 --> 10:11.400
I'M FINALLY GONNA GET
A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP

10:11.400 --> 10:13.000
AND GO BACK
TO MY NORMAL DREAM.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.600
THE ONE WHERE YOU WIN
THE MISS COSTA RICA PAGEANT?

10:15.600 --> 10:18.600
I WISH PEACE FOR ALL
THE LITTLE <i>NIÑOS. </i>

10:22.467 --> 10:24.934
DUDE!

10:24.934 --> 10:26.600
LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

10:26.600 --> 10:29.400
OH, THERE IS JUST NO WAY
THAT I CAN AFFORD THIS.

10:29.400 --> 10:30.900
PAY WHATEVER YOU CAN.

10:30.900 --> 10:33.033
IT GETS A LITTLE
LONELY AROUND HERE.

10:33.033 --> 10:35.367
I JUST CAN'T SEEM
TO KEEP A ROOMMATE.

10:35.367 --> 10:37.100
WHAT?

10:37.100 --> 10:38.834
YOU CAN'T KEEP A ROOMMATE
IN A PLACE LIKE THIS?

10:38.834 --> 10:40.600
OH, WAIT A SECOND,
I KNOW. BAD NEIGHBORS.

10:40.600 --> 10:41.700
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

10:41.700 --> 10:43.000
COME IN.

10:44.133 --> 10:45.900
OH, HEY, SHEILA.

10:45.900 --> 10:48.500
HI, ADAM. THIS PACKAGE
CAME FOR YOU TODAY.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.600
I SIGNED FOR IT.

10:51.033 --> 10:53.100
WHO'S THE CUTIE?

10:53.100 --> 10:55.200
ERIC MATTHEWS,
SHEILA SHAGHER.

10:55.200 --> 10:58.200
OH, BEHAVE.

10:58.200 --> 11:00.900
SHEILA LIVES NEXT DOOR.
ERIC'S MY NEW ROOMMATE.

11:00.900 --> 11:03.200
WELL, I HAVE
TO COME AROUND
MORE OFTEN

11:03.200 --> 11:05.033
TO BORROW
A CUP OF SUGAR.

11:05.033 --> 11:06.700
WHY STOP AT A CUP?

11:06.700 --> 11:11.100
WELL, I HAVE TO RUN,
BUT IT WAS NICE
MEETING YOU.

11:11.100 --> 11:12.300
YOU, TOO.

11:17.734 --> 11:20.300
DUDE, DUDE,
DUDE, DUDE, DUDE!

11:20.300 --> 11:23.100
HOW IS IT YOU HAVE
ANY TROUBLE AT ALL
KEEPING A ROOMMATE?

11:23.100 --> 11:24.800
BEATS ME.

11:31.834 --> 11:33.000
AAAAHHH!

11:36.300 --> 11:37.367
NOT AGAIN.

11:38.900 --> 11:40.100
IT WAS RAINING.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.100
YOU HAD A NEW UMBRELLA.

11:43.100 --> 11:45.767
YOU LET ME
TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

11:45.767 --> 11:49.400
AND THEN I SHOVED IT
DOWN YOUR THROAT...

11:49.400 --> 11:51.000
AND I OPENED IT.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.800
YOU OPENED IT?

11:53.800 --> 11:58.567
OH, SHAWN,
I MARY POPPINED YOU.

11:58.567 --> 12:02.734
WHY? WHY?

12:03.934 --> 12:05.300
WHY?

12:05.300 --> 12:07.033
CORY, IT'S THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT.

12:07.033 --> 12:08.467
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

12:15.200 --> 12:16.734
YOU GAVE ME
BAD ADVICE, FEENY.

12:16.734 --> 12:18.867
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

12:18.867 --> 12:21.233
YOU WERE IN
MY DREAM, MR. FEENY,

12:21.233 --> 12:24.834
AND YOU GAVE ME
ADVICE THAT SUCKED.

12:24.834 --> 12:28.567
I'M NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR DREAM FEENY.

12:28.567 --> 12:31.100
WHY DON'T YOU START
FROM THE BEGINNING?

12:31.100 --> 12:32.500
EVERYTIME I FALL ASLEEP,

12:32.500 --> 12:34.400
I DREAM THAT
I KILL SHAWN.

12:34.400 --> 12:35.967
NOW WHAT
KIND OF PERSON AM I

12:35.967 --> 12:39.200
THAT WOULD WANT
MY BEST FRIEND DEAD?

12:39.200 --> 12:41.834
WELL, NOW,
YOU KNOW THAT YOU
DON'T WANT SHAWN DEAD.

12:41.834 --> 12:44.300
OH, HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHO I WANT DEAD?

12:44.300 --> 12:47.967
CORY, YOU MUSTN'T
TAKE DREAMS LITERALLY.

12:47.967 --> 12:50.700
THEY CAN BE INTERPRETED
IN MANY WAYS.

12:50.700 --> 12:52.700
WHY AM I KILLING SHAWN?

12:52.700 --> 12:54.200
I REALLY DON'T KNOW.

12:54.200 --> 12:56.600
YOU KNOW, FREUD
SAYS THAT, UH,

12:56.600 --> 12:58.800
DREAMS COME FROM
OUR UNCONSCIOUS.

12:58.800 --> 13:01.200
REPRESSED THOUGHTS THAT
HAVE TO BE CONFRONTED.

13:01.200 --> 13:04.734
BUT IN THE DREAM STATE,
THEY'RE NOT QUITE CLEAR.

13:04.734 --> 13:08.000
IT'S QUITE CLEAR
I'M KILLING SHAWN.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.934
YOU'RE DREAMING
ABOUT IT FOR A REASON.

13:10.934 --> 13:12.667
WHAT'S THE REASON?

13:12.667 --> 13:16.367
WELL, YOU WAKE UP
EVERY TIME SCREAMING?

13:16.367 --> 13:17.667
YEAH.

13:17.667 --> 13:19.300
AFTER YOU KILL SHAWN?

13:19.300 --> 13:23.200
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I'VE NEVER SEEN
HIM DIE,

13:23.200 --> 13:26.100
BUT, I MEAN, I DID
SOME PRETTY BAD STUFF
TO HIM, MR. FEENY.

13:26.100 --> 13:27.767
HE DIDN'T
STAND A CHANCE.

13:27.767 --> 13:32.800
OH, SO YOU ALWAYS
WOKE UP BEFORE YOU
ACTUALLY KILLED HIM?

13:32.800 --> 13:34.934
YEAH, BUT, I...

13:34.934 --> 13:37.367
YOU'RE RIGHT.

13:37.367 --> 13:39.233
I'VE NEVER
FINISHED THE DREAM.

13:39.233 --> 13:41.767
THAT'S THE KEY,
MR. MATTHEWS.

13:41.767 --> 13:43.600
PERHAPS IF YOU
FINISH THE DREAM,

13:43.600 --> 13:45.300
YOU'LL FIND OUT
WHAT IT MEANS.

13:50.600 --> 13:53.133
DUDE, THAT WHOLE
BEDROOM'S FOR ME?

13:53.133 --> 13:54.867
IT'S BIGGER THAN
MY PARENTS' HOUSE.

13:54.867 --> 13:56.300
WHAT ARE YOU WATCHING?

13:56.300 --> 13:57.600
WEATHER CHANNEL.

13:57.600 --> 13:59.000
WANT TO JOIN ME?

13:59.000 --> 14:00.100
SURE.

14:01.467 --> 14:04.367
WHOA! NOT THERE.

14:04.367 --> 14:05.900
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

14:05.900 --> 14:06.900
MY MOTHER'S CHAIR.

14:06.900 --> 14:08.600
OH, SORRY.
SHE COMING OVER?

14:08.600 --> 14:09.700
SHE'S DEAD.

14:09.700 --> 14:12.200
OH, I'M SORRY, MAN.

14:12.200 --> 14:13.367
THANK YOU.

14:13.367 --> 14:14.700
I LOVE HER VERY MUCH.

14:15.834 --> 14:17.300
I'LL JUST GO
CRASH OVER THERE.

14:21.400 --> 14:22.734
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

14:22.734 --> 14:24.600
ERIC, WILL YOU
GET THAT, PLEASE?

14:24.600 --> 14:25.600
YEAH.

14:27.233 --> 14:28.233
HELLO?

14:28.233 --> 14:30.100
ERIC, IT'S ME, ADAM.

14:31.600 --> 14:33.400
YOU CAN'T
SIT THERE, EITHER.

14:37.033 --> 14:38.600
DUDE, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

14:38.600 --> 14:40.700
[WHISPERING]
Eric, I'm on the phone.

14:42.900 --> 14:44.033
ERIC?

14:48.300 --> 14:49.600
YES, ADAM?

14:51.200 --> 14:52.734
THAT'S WHERE
UNCLE DAVE DIED.

14:57.500 --> 14:59.600
[CUCKOO CLOCK CHIMING]

14:59.600 --> 15:01.200
IT'S TIME TO
FEED THE BIRD.

15:01.200 --> 15:02.200
WE HAVE A BIRD?

15:02.200 --> 15:03.767
HOW COME I HAVEN'T
SEEN THIS BIRD?

15:03.767 --> 15:05.200
WANT TO HELP ME
FEED HER?

15:05.200 --> 15:06.800
YEAH, MAN. I LOVE BIRDS.

15:06.800 --> 15:07.967
ALL KINDS OF BIRDS?

15:07.967 --> 15:09.367
EVERY ONE OF THEM.

15:09.367 --> 15:11.400
OK.

15:11.400 --> 15:13.000
WHERE'S THE BIRDY?

15:13.000 --> 15:14.400
WHERE'S THE PRETTY BIRDY?

15:14.400 --> 15:15.967
WHERE'S THE PRETTY BIR--

15:18.800 --> 15:20.300
HER NAME'S NELLIE.

15:20.300 --> 15:22.233
I'VE HAD HER
SINCE I WAS 2.

15:22.233 --> 15:25.967
SHE'S THE BEST
BIRD EVER.

15:25.967 --> 15:28.300
SHE NORMALLY
DOESN'T LIKE PEOPLE,

15:28.300 --> 15:30.467
BUT LOOK AT HER,

15:30.467 --> 15:32.100
SHE SURE LIKES YOU.

15:32.100 --> 15:34.300
POLLY WANT A CRACKER?

15:34.300 --> 15:37.600
POLLY WANT AN AUTOPSY!

15:37.600 --> 15:39.467
THAT'S A DEAD BIRD!

15:39.467 --> 15:40.967
NOT TO ME.

15:40.967 --> 15:42.667
THAT IS JUST
SICK AND WEIRD.

15:42.667 --> 15:43.934
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOU?

15:43.934 --> 15:45.100
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU,

15:45.100 --> 15:47.367
TALKING IN FRONT
OF HER LIKE THAT?

15:47.367 --> 15:49.467
SORRY, NELLIE.

15:49.467 --> 15:52.500
[AS PARROT]
IT'S NOT
YOUR FAULT, ADAM.

15:52.500 --> 15:54.367
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT.

15:54.367 --> 15:55.734
I'M OUT OF HERE.

15:55.734 --> 15:57.133
[WHISPERING]
And it is so his fault.

15:57.133 --> 15:59.300
GREAT. LEAVE!

15:59.300 --> 16:01.000
EVERYBODY LEAVES ME.

16:01.000 --> 16:03.600
I WONDER WHY!

16:03.600 --> 16:05.000
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE DIFFERENT.

16:05.000 --> 16:06.300
YOU'RE JUST LIKE
EVERYBODY ELSE.

16:06.300 --> 16:09.100
NOBODY CARES ABOUT ME.
NOBODY WANTS ME.

16:09.100 --> 16:13.000
FOREVER ALONE.
I HATE THE SILENCE.

16:14.667 --> 16:16.200
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

16:16.200 --> 16:17.233
NO, YOU DON'T.

16:17.233 --> 16:20.033
YEAH, I REALLY DO.

16:20.033 --> 16:22.100
I WAS KICKED OUT
BY MY FAMILY,

16:22.100 --> 16:23.734
BETRAYED BY
MY CLOSEST FRIENDS,

16:23.734 --> 16:26.233
THROWN OUT INTO
THIS CRAZY WORLD
ALL BY MYSELF.

16:26.233 --> 16:29.467
NOWHERE TO GO,
NOWHERE TO LIVE,

16:29.467 --> 16:30.567
ALONE.

16:30.567 --> 16:32.767
SO, YOU'LL STAY?

16:32.767 --> 16:34.000
NO.

16:36.033 --> 16:37.600
HI, ERIC.

16:37.600 --> 16:40.867
I DID IT AGAIN.
LOCKED MYSELF OUT
AFTER TAKING A SHOWER.

16:40.867 --> 16:45.400
AT LEAST THIS TIME
I REMEMBERED THE TOWEL.

16:45.400 --> 16:46.500
MIND IF I HANG
WITH YOU GUYS

16:46.500 --> 16:48.300
TILL MY ROOMMATE
COMES BACK?

16:48.300 --> 16:49.934
MAYBE I'LL STAY.

16:49.934 --> 16:53.000
[AS PARROT] ADAM,
HE'S GONNA STAY.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.233
HELLO, HELLO.

17:01.233 --> 17:02.400
YOU SEE, SHAWN,

17:02.400 --> 17:04.000
ALL IT TOOK
WAS YOU AND ME

17:04.000 --> 17:05.500
TO GET THEM TO SETTLE
THEIR DIFFERENCES.

17:05.500 --> 17:07.200
CORY AND SHAWN FOREVER.

17:07.200 --> 17:08.500
BEST FRIENDS.

17:08.500 --> 17:10.767
BEST FRIENDS FOREVER.

17:14.233 --> 17:16.967
CORY, WHY ARE YOU
LOOKING AT ME LIKE THAT?

17:16.967 --> 17:17.900
CORY, WHAT--

17:20.400 --> 17:21.567
CORY!

17:21.567 --> 17:22.834
YOU HAVE TO GO.

17:26.000 --> 17:27.834
AAAAAHH!

17:29.567 --> 17:30.834
SHAWN!

17:32.600 --> 17:34.100
SHAWWWWNNN!

17:35.500 --> 17:37.133
CORY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

17:37.133 --> 17:39.033
SHOVING EVERYONE DOWN
THE ELEVATOR SHAFT.

17:39.033 --> 17:40.133
GUESS WHO'S NEXT.

17:40.133 --> 17:41.967
AAAAAHHH!

17:41.967 --> 17:43.300
RACHEL!

17:43.300 --> 17:46.767
RACHELLL--AAAAAHHH!

17:46.767 --> 17:48.467
ANGELA, COME ON.

17:48.467 --> 17:50.000
EVERYBODY'S DOING IT.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.200
DOING WHAT?

17:52.200 --> 17:53.367
THIS.

17:53.367 --> 17:54.467
AAAAAAAHHH!

17:58.500 --> 17:59.500
Lauren: HI, CORY.

18:01.400 --> 18:02.667
LAUREN?

18:02.667 --> 18:04.300
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:04.300 --> 18:06.700
I'M OVER YOU.
YOU SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

18:08.100 --> 18:09.734
I'M NOT LAUREN.

18:09.734 --> 18:12.467
THEN WHO ARE YOU?

18:12.467 --> 18:14.200
I'M EVERYTHING
YOU'RE GIVING UP.

18:14.200 --> 18:16.233
THE GIRLS YOU'LL
NEVER GET TO MEET.

18:16.233 --> 18:18.900
THE PLACES YOU'LL
NEVER GET TO GO.

18:18.900 --> 18:21.600
THE LIFE
YOU'LL NEVER HAVE.

18:23.000 --> 18:24.600
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

18:26.033 --> 18:27.300
BYE, CORY.

18:30.900 --> 18:31.867
WAIT!

18:33.000 --> 18:34.233
Topanga: CORY?

18:37.500 --> 18:38.767
TOPANGA?

18:41.834 --> 18:43.734
WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

18:45.567 --> 18:47.200
I KILLED THEM.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.734
FOR US.

18:51.734 --> 18:53.567
I KNOW.

18:58.133 --> 18:59.600
I MISS THEM.

18:59.600 --> 19:01.600
I MISS THEM, TOO.

19:07.033 --> 19:08.767
YOU CAN WAKE UP NOW.

19:12.700 --> 19:14.033
CORY?

19:14.033 --> 19:16.300
CORY, WAKE UP. YOU'VE BEEN
SLEEPING ALL NIGHT.

19:17.800 --> 19:19.000
MORNING, SUNSHINE.

19:19.000 --> 19:20.400
HEY.

19:20.400 --> 19:21.734
DID YOU DREAM?

19:21.734 --> 19:23.000
YEAH.

19:23.000 --> 19:24.500
WHAT DID YOU
DREAM ABOUT?

19:24.500 --> 19:27.567
I DREAMT
ABOUT YOU.

19:27.567 --> 19:31.400
OH, GOOD.
SO YOU'RE OK NOW?

19:31.400 --> 19:32.867
YEAH, I'M FINE.

19:32.867 --> 19:35.700
GOOD.
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

19:35.700 --> 19:37.000
BYE.
BYE.

19:41.033 --> 19:42.667
YOU'RE NOT OK, ARE YOU?

19:42.667 --> 19:44.900
DO YOU THINK I'M
RUSHING INTO MARRIAGE?

19:44.900 --> 19:49.133
YOU'VE BEEN RUSHING
INTO MARRIAGE SINCE
YOU WERE 2 YEARS OLD.

19:49.133 --> 19:52.567
I MEAN, NOTHING'S
GONNA CHANGE BETWEEN
YOU AND ME, IS IT?

19:52.567 --> 19:55.734
IS THAT WHAT YOU'VE
BEEN DREAMING ABOUT?

19:55.734 --> 19:57.667
NO, I'M JUST...

19:57.667 --> 20:01.867
I GUESS I'M AFRAID
THAT AFTER I GET MARRIED

20:01.867 --> 20:03.300
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA CHANGE.

20:03.300 --> 20:06.567
WELL, YEAH, IT WILL.
IT HAS TO.

20:06.567 --> 20:09.500
I DON'T WANT IT TO.

20:19.800 --> 20:21.867
OK, NELLIE. OK, BEG.

20:21.867 --> 20:23.500
OK, NOW ROLL OVER.

20:23.500 --> 20:24.934
OK.

20:24.934 --> 20:26.900
HEY, PLAY DEAD,
PLAY DEAD.

20:26.900 --> 20:29.200
HO, HO, OK.

20:29.200 --> 20:31.300
GOOD BIRD, GOOD BIRD!

20:31.300 --> 20:32.734
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

20:34.500 --> 20:35.934
HELLO.

20:35.934 --> 20:37.467
ERIC, IT'S ME, ADAM.

20:37.467 --> 20:39.100
HEY, MAN, WHAT'S UP?

20:39.100 --> 20:41.100
I JUST THINK
IT'S GREAT HOW
YOU AND NELLIE

20:41.100 --> 20:42.300
HAVE BEEN GETTING
ALONG SO WELL.

20:42.300 --> 20:45.100
YEAH, WELL,
I LOVE POULTRY.

20:45.100 --> 20:48.867
ANYWAY, I MEAN YOU
AND I HAVE BEEN GETTING
ALONG SO WELL THAT--

20:48.867 --> 20:50.500
EXCUSE ME.
OH, SORRY.

20:50.500 --> 20:53.934
THAT I THINK IT'S TIME
YOU FINALLY MET MY MOM.

20:53.934 --> 20:55.500
YOUR MOM?

20:55.500 --> 20:57.600
LOOK, DUDE, I THOUGHT
THAT YOUR MOTHER WAS--

20:57.600 --> 21:01.233
MOM, I WANT YOU
TO MEET MY NEW ROOMMATE.

21:01.233 --> 21:03.667
Adam, woman's voice:
IS HE A GOOD BOY?

21:05.600 --> 21:07.233
HE'S A VERY GOOD BOY.

21:07.233 --> 21:09.100
Adam, woman's voice:
I'M GLAD BECAUSE
YOUR LAST ROOMMMATE

21:09.100 --> 21:11.967
WAS A VERY,
VERY BAD BOY.

21:11.967 --> 21:15.100
THAT'S WHY I TOOK CARE
OF HIM FOR YOU, MOM.

21:15.100 --> 21:18.800
Adam, man's voice:
WHAT? YOU DON'T SAY
HELLO TO YOUR GRANDPA?
